General Notes:
Some of the Officers Rules need splitting up... there should be a rule
defining the Office in the Pl set, and a rule defining duties of the
Office in the Pr set.

Much of the Pr set is made up of two large classes of rules--Rules which
define Crimes, and Rules which define ASAP actions.  There are a few
exceptions.

A *whole lot* of otherwise-Platonic Rules require Reporting of some
transfer... I've put these in the Pl set, although they should probably
be fixed up a bit.

In general, I think, most of the fundamental rule-change rules should be
Pl, although some of the exact mechanics will be Pr.

Obviously, rules which require a Player to do something are Pr.  But
what about Rules which denote a bonus for a Player?  I think they're Pl,
but I'm not sure.

Re: the "legal" debate--a _lot_ of the Pl rules use the word 'legal'.

Note: I'm skipping the entire Courts section of the Ruleset, because my
copy of the Ruleset is pre-Court reform.  Has Chuck published another
one?
